    <text id="B1195T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Watts, a lawyer in Staunton, appeals that Roswell Waldo's order to transfer to
                    Wytheville be revoked, observing Waldo's excellent performance as the Bureau's
                    agent in Augusta County.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="General">Gen'l</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> &amp;c</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have just learned from Roswell Waldo, <unclear>Esq</unclear>, <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.Comr.</abbr>, here, that
                    he has been ordered to report at Wytheville for duty. And having been a close
                    observer of him, &amp; his promptitude in the dispatch of business involved
                    by his position, permit me to express my deep regret at his ordered removal from
                    the office here, and further, to express a <pb n="2"/>hope that the order will
                    be recalled, &amp; he continued in his place: I have reason to believe he
                    has given entire, general satisfaction, to all interests concerned.</p>

                <p>I have been here for over thirty years, &amp; most of that time a member of
                    the Bar: And I do think I have a right to think I can with propriety make the
                    appeal herein, to you.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Truly, your <abbr expan="obedient Servant">obt Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John B. Watts</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
